# Agent Color Pipeline Research Report
## Task 43 / Subtask 95 — Confirm line numbers and code patterns

Generated: 2026-04-10

---

## Summary

All 5 files verified. Line numbers from the earlier task brief are accurate (within 0-2 lines). There are **4 sites** in agents.go that pass `agent.Color` to `lipgloss.Color()`. Only **1 of 4** has an empty-string guard (line 500). The other 3 will pass empty strings directly to `lipgloss.Color("")`, which renders as the terminal default (no visible color — the dot becomes invisible or blends with background). No validation exists anywhere in the parse or store pipeline.

---

## Findings per File

### 1. tui/internal/model/agents.go — Color Render Sites

**Site A: Line 391** — Agent list dot (left panel)
```go
// Line 389-396
selected := m.focused && m.leftFocused && flatIdx == m.cursor

// Agent row: colored dot + name
dot := lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color(a.Color)).Render("◆")
nameStyle := lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(t.Text)
if selected {
    nameStyle = nameStyle.Bold(true)
}
```
- **Guard:** NONE. Passes `a.Color` directly.
- **Fallback:** `lipgloss.Color("")` → terminal default foreground → dot may be invisible.

**Site B: Lines 500-503** — Detail panel color field (right panel)
```go
// Line 500-503
if agent.Color != "" {
    colorDot := lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color(agent.Color)).Render("◆")
    fields = append(fields, labelStyle.Render("Color")+"  "+colorDot+" "+t.Dim.Render(agent.Color))
}
```
- **Guard:** YES — `if agent.Color != ""` wrapping the entire block.
- **Fallback:** Skips rendering the Color field entirely if empty.
- **This is the pattern to replicate at the other 3 sites.**

**Site C: Line 556** — Right panel title dot (scrollHeight calculation)
